This is like throwing a cat and a dog in a closet and hoping everything turns out OK.



Due to the rapid growth of NC and the dynamics of the retiring baby-boomers, this “user conflict” will only get worse with time. Ask the DMF, they will tell you the same thing. This bill obviously will not make everyone happy, but it brings cash mitigation to the table, and ultimately will end most of the user conflict.



This is finally one issue that rises high above party politics. All the imposing factors demand action. We are fishermen from all walks of life, Republican and Democrat hand in hand with the same goals. Please support H 918, the Coastal Game Fish Act!



